"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847015","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-02","<p>The Government does not produce forecasts for job creation over a future time period for the renewables industry.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-03-02T11:10:08.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847015/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847015/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847015/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-22","Renewable Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what estimate the Government has made of the number of jobs which will be created by the renewables industry over the next ten years.","false","Biography information for Dr Sarah Wollaston","Totnes","Dr Sarah Wollaston","129189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847016","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-02","<p>It is up to the operator to agree disposal methods with the appropriate regulators as part of their planning application for any future shale gas development.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-03-02T11:06:37.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847016/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847016/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847016/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-22","Fracking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the implementation unit report on shale gas extraction, what disposal method will be used for flowback waste from (a) the 17 sites by 2020, (b) the 30 to 35 sites by 2022 and (c) the 155 sites by 2025.","false","Biography information for Dr Sarah Wollaston","Totnes","Dr Sarah Wollaston","129190"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847017","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-02","<p>The Government has not made an assessment of the amount of flowback waste which would be produced from any future shale gas development.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-03-02T11:07:32.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847017/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847017/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847017/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-22","Fracking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the Implementation Unit Report on Shale Gas, what estimate the Government has made of the amount of flowback waste which would need to be disposed of for the projected (a) 17 sites by 2020, (b) 30-35 sites by 2022 and (c) 155 sites by 2025.","false","Biography information for Dr Sarah Wollaston","Totnes","Dr Sarah Wollaston","129191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847018","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-02","<p>It is the operator’s responsibility to agree disposal methods with the appropriate regulators as part of their planning application for all shale gas development.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-03-02T11:11:11.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847018/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847018/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847018/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-22","Fracking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the Implementation Unit Report on Shale Gas, which disposal method is planned to be used for the projected (a) 17 sites by 2020, (b) 30-35 sites by 2022 and (c) 155 sites by 2025.","false","Biography information for Dr Sarah Wollaston","Totnes","Dr Sarah Wollaston","129192"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847019","Home Office","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Home Office publishes station numbers, provided by The Chartered Institute of Public Finance and Accountancy (CIPFA), here <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fire-statistics-data-tables" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fire-statistics-data-tables</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-03-01T19:19:06.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847019/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847019/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847019/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-22","Fire Stations: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many operational fire stations there have been in the West Midlands in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","129193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847020","Home Office","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes firefighter statistics and publishes population statistics for fire and rescue authorities using the Office for National Statistics’ Mid Year Estimates.</p><p>The former are currently available to March 2017 and the latter to June 2016 and can be found here <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fire-statistics-data-tables" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fire-statistics-data-tables</a> in tables FIRE1101 and FIRE1401.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-03-01T19:15:51.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847020/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847020/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847020/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-22","Fire and Rescue Services: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many firefighters per 100,000 residents there were in the West Midlands in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","129194"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847021","Home Office","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Government consulted all Local Authorities on the provisional Local Government Settlement which was published in December 2017. All responses were considered in advance of laying the Final Local Government Settlement which was debated and approved by the House on 7 February.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-03-01T19:30:02.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847021/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847021/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847021/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-22","West Midlands Fire Service: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent discussions she has had with the West Midlands Fire Authority on funding for the West Midlands Fire Service.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","129195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847022","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Department has received and responded to several letters from Birmingham City councillors about general works they are undertaking to enhance the safety of their residential blocks.</p><p>If any local authority has carried out assessments and identified essential measures to address building specific issues, then they should get in touch with the Department with further details. This will allow Department officials to discuss the position and work with them on the way forward.</p><p> </p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-02-27T17:41:29.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847022/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847022/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847022/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-02-22","High Rise Flats: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what recent representations he has received from Birmingham City Council on funding to carry out extensive works to 213 tower blocks on the advice of West Midlands Fire Service; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","129196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847023","Home Office","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Home Office does not hold this information. Decisions about the most effective use of available resources, including the number and operating hours of police stations, are a matter for Police and Crime Commissioners and Chief Constables locally, tailored to the needs of the local community.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-03-01T19:17:25.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847023/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847023/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847023/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-22","Police Stations: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many operational police stations there were in the West Midlands in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","129197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847024","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-02-28","<p>The Voluntary Right to Buy Midlands pilot will give thousands more housing association tenants the opportunity to enjoy the benefits of home ownership. The Government is currently engaging with the National Housing Federation and housing associations in the Midlands, and more details on the pilot will be announced in due course.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-02-28T17:09:51.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847024/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847024/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847024/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-02-22","Right to Buy Scheme: Birmingham Northfield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will list the housing associations within Birmingham Northfield constituency that are eligible for the regional pilot of the Right to Buy for housing association tenants.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","129198"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847025","Home Office","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes firefighter and incident attended statistics. The former are currently available to March 2017 and the latter to September 2017 and can be found here <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fire-statistics-data-tables" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fire-statistics-data-tables</a> in tables FIRE0102 and FIRE1101.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-03-01T19:21:24.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847025/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847025/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847025/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-22","Fire and Rescue Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent assessment she has of trends in the comparative number of (a) incidents attended by fire services and (b) fire-fighters in (i) the West Midlands and (ii) England.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","129199"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847026","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-05","<p>The Department has not made an assessment of the equity of the level of funding for public transport throughout the UK.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not allocate funding to transport on a ‘per head of population’ basis. Decisions are made based on a rigorous and fair appraisal process that ensures spending goes to the projects and programmes where it is most needed and delivers greatest value-for-money for both taxpayers and passengers.</p><p> </p><p>Data from the HM Treasury Country and Regional Analysis (CRA) provides figures for total public expenditure on transport and how this varies across regions. The latest publication is available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/country-and-regional-analysis-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/country-and-regional-analysis-2017</a>.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-03-05T17:17:24.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847026/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847026/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847026/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-22","Public Transport: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the equity of the level of funding for public transport throughout the UK.","false","Biography information for Laura Pidcock","North West Durham","Laura Pidcock","129200"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847027","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>Our Embassy in Khartoum is aware of two dual British-Sudanese nationals that have been detained following recent protests in Sudan. We continue to press the Government of Sudan to allow consular access to these two individuals, as well as to one dual Australian-Sudanese national as part of the UK’s agreement to provide consular assistance to Australian nationals in Sudan.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-02-27T16:40:13.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847027/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847027/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847027/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-22","Sudan: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what estimate he has made of the number of British citizens currently detained in Sudan following the protests that began on 7 January 2018.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","129201"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847028","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>We understand that many of those detained following recent protests have had some access to legal advice. We continue to make clear to the Government of Sudan our expectation that all detainees will be treated in accordance with international standards, which includes full access to legal advice.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-02-27T16:43:07.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847028/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847028/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847028/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-22","Sudan: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the level of access to legal advice for detainees in Sudan following the protests that began on 7 January 2018.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","129202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847029","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-05","<p>The Government is providing significant levels of funding to support public transport across the North East. For example, we have committed to provide £337 million towards the cost of replacing the entire rolling stock fleet on the Tyne and Wear Metro. My Department has also provided both revenue and capital funding to the Metro since its inception in 1980, and currently provides £55 million a year towards day-to-day operational costs and an Asset Renewal Programme.</p><p> </p><p>We are also taking steps to improve rail connectivity in the North East. The Northern franchise will see a new high quality Northern Connect service operate at least 10 times per day between Middlesbrough and Carlisle via Newcastle, with Hexham and the MetroCentre becoming Northern Connect stations with staff, WiFi and catering outlets. The Transpennine franchise will see the introduction of a new hourly service between Newcastle and Edinburgh, along with an increase in the frequency of trains between Newcastle and York/Leeds/Manchester from one to two trains per hour.</p><p> </p><p>The North East will also benefit from the £250 million being paid this year to support bus services in England through Bus Service Operators Grant (BSOG). Around £40 million of this BSOG funding is paid directly to local authorities, rather than bus operators to help deliver bus services. The Government also provides almost £1 billion of funding for the concessionary bus pass every year, and remains committed to the scheme.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, we have recently announced that the Tees Valley Combined Authority will receive a per capita allocation of £59 million from the new £1.7 billion Transforming Cities Fund to improve intra-urban connectivity. Other cities in the North East without a Metro Mayor may be able to benefit from the competitive part of the Fund, which will be launched shortly.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-03-05T17:15:39.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847029/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847029/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847029/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-22","Public Transport: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent assessment he has made of whether there is a need to increase funding for public transport in the North East.","false","Biography information for Laura Pidcock","North West Durham","Laura Pidcock","129203"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847030","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-02","<p>The bus market outside London is deregulated and decisions regarding service provision is primarily a commercial matter for bus operators. Decisions on subsidised bus services are a matter for individual English local authorities, in the light of their other spending priorities.</p><p> </p><p>However, my Department provides around £40m of Bus Subsidy Operators Grant (BSOG) directly to English local authorities for local bus services, of which Durham receives around £347,000. BSOG plays an especially important role in protecting services in rural areas by helping extend the bus network, providing residents with vital links to local services.</p><p> </p><p>The Bus Services Act 2017 introduces a number of new tools to help local authorities improve local bus services in their area. Through partnership arrangements we have enabled local authorities and bus operators to work constructively to provide better services for passengers.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-03-02T11:09:54.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847030/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847030/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847030/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-22","Bus Services: North West Durham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to improve bus links in North West Durham constituency.","false","Biography information for Laura Pidcock","North West Durham","Laura Pidcock","129204"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847031","Home Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>All Authorised Firearms Officers must undertake the National Police Firearms Training Curriculum – a programme of nationally accredited training for armed officers.</p><p>The length of courses varies according to the duties likely to be undertaken. Including in respect to Operation Temperer, deployment decisions and the length of associated armed officer training are operational matters for the police.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-02-27T17:50:51.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847031/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847031/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847031/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-22","Police: Firearms","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 20 February 2018 to Question 127226 on Police: Firearms, what assessment she has made of the effect of differences in the length of firearms training received by Authorised Firearms Officers on deployment decisions in respect of Operation Temperer.","false","Biography information for Holly Lynch","Halifax","Holly Lynch","129205"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847032","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>During his visit in February 2018 to Burma the Foreign Secretary saw first-hand Rohingya villages which had been razed. The FCO accepts that has been ethnic cleansing. The Foreign Secretary expressed his deep concern over the human tragedy of the Rohingya to State Counsellor Aung San Suu Kyi during their meeting in Naypyidaw on 11 February. He lobbied that Burmese authorities carry out a full, credible and independent investigation into the violence in Rakhine and hold to account those responsible for human rights violations.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-02-27T17:39:24.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847032/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847032/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847032/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-22","Burma: Rohingya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to the Burmese Government on allegations of the bulldozing of Rohingya mass graves; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","129206"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847033","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-05","<p>The Future Accommodation Model (FAM) Survey was conducted in 2016 to gauge the views of serving Armed Forces personnel on current accommodation provision and proposed options under FAM.</p><p> </p><p>The Survey was open to approximately 137,000 personnel. The response rate was 18%, based on 24,302 valid responses. Full details of the methodology used in the FAM survey can be found at the following address:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mod-future-accommodation-model-survey-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mod-future-accommodation-model-survey-2016</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Response rates tended to be lower among the more junior ranks, which means these groups are under-represented within the data. To compensate for this non-response bias, FAM Survey results were weighted by Service, Rank and Marital Status as the key variables affecting both responses rates and views on FAM.</p><p> </p><p>The results are now being considered alongside qualitative data, collected from focus groups and workshops, and quantitative data from other surveys.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-03-05T16:58:39.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847033/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847033/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847033/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-22","Armed Forces: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Future Accommodation Model survey, what assessment he has made of the effect of the level  survey’s response rate on the efficacy of the survey’s results and conclusions.","false","Biography information for Faisal Rashid","Warrington South","Faisal Rashid","129207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847034","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-12","<p>Public sector procurers are required to assess value for money using criteria linked to the subject matter of the contract, including compliance with the published specification.</p><p> </p><p>Regulations covering selection and award criteria are included in the Public Contracts Regulations 2015:</p><p><a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2015/102/contents/made" target="_blank">http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2015/102/contents/made</a></p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-03-12T13:58:01.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847034/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847034/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847034/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-22","Government Departments: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what criteria the Government uses to award contracts to private companies.","false","Biography information for Faisal Rashid","Warrington South","Faisal Rashid","129208"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847035","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-01","<p>Table A shows all of the options considered by the Government during the passage of the Pensions Act 2011. At the time the options were prioritised for costing, and those which were less specific in scope were not costed.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2018-03-01T15:44:32.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847035/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847035/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847035/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-22","State Retirement Pensions: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to her Department’s response to Freedom of Information request 378/2016, for what reasons transitional arrangements No. 22 and 23 of Table A have not been costed.","false","Biography information for Faisal Rashid","Warrington South","Faisal Rashid","129209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847036","HM Treasury","false","2018-02-27","<p>This information is not held centrally by HMRC and cannot be provided.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-02-27T15:53:07.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847036/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847036/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847036/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-22","Child Benefit: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received relief from tax expenditure on child benefit in (a) 2015-16, (b) 2016-17 and (c) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","129210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847037","HM Treasury","false","2018-02-27","<p>The table below shows estimates for the number of people receiving income tax or National Insurance Contributions relief for each of the requested allowances. The estimates show people that would face a higher tax liability if the individual allowances and/or thresholds were removed, (and includes people who are currently non-taxpayers as their income is covered by these thresholds and/or allowances).</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="4"><p>Estimates of the number of people who received tax relief (Millions)<sup> (1)</sup></p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>2017-18</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Disability living allowance</p></td><td><p>3.4</p></td><td><p>3.4</p></td><td><p>3.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Attendance allowance</p></td><td><p>1.5</p></td><td><p>1.5</p></td><td><p>1.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>War disablement benefits</p></td><td><p>0.1</p></td><td><p>0.1</p></td><td><p>0.1</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4"><p>(1) The figures are rounded to the nearest hundred thousand and presented in millions.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>Estimates are based on the 2015-16 Family Resource Survey (FRS), projected to 2016-17 and 2017-18 using forecast benefit expenditure and caseload data consistent with the Department of Work and Pension (DWP) Spring Budget 2017 outlook.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","129212 ; 129213","2018-02-27T16:02:49.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847037/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847037/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847037/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-22","Attendance Allowance: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received relief from tax expenditure on attendance allowance in (a) 2015-16, (b) 2016-17 and (c) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","129211"
