"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847040","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-01","<p>Before responding to the Knight Review of electronic balloting for industrial action the Government is required by Section 4 of the Trade Union Act 2016 to “consult relevant organisations, including professionals from expert associations, to seek their advice and recommendations.” We are currently assessing the best means of obtaining this advice.</p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-03-01T11:16:18.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847040/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847040/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847040/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-22","Industrial Disputes: Ballots","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what progress has been made on e-balloting pilots as recommended by the 2017 Knight Review.","false","Biography information for Laura Pidcock","North West Durham","Laura Pidcock","129214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847041","HM Treasury","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Government has no plans to introduce such grants. The UK supports international efforts to tackle aggressive tax avoidance and evasion, and supports lists of non-co-operative jurisdictions for tax purposes in the OECD and EU to encourage jurisdictions to comply with relevant international tax standards. The UK also supports capacity building programmes to help jurisdictions implement these standards, including through the OECD’s Global Forum, the OECD’s Inclusive Framework on Base Erosion and Profit Shifting, and a dedicated capacity building unit in HMRC.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-03-01T14:52:37.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847041/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847041/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847041/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-22","Tax Havens","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential merit of the introduction of favourable financial grants to rebuild and diversify the economies of tax havens that are conditional on benchmarks on (a) transparency, (b) accountability and (c) cooperation to tackle offshore tax avoidance and evasion.","false","Biography information for Faisal Rashid","Warrington South","Faisal Rashid","129215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847042","HM Treasury","false","2018-03-01","<p>Government has taken significant steps to tackle multinational avoidance. That includes the introduction of the diverted profits tax, which raised over £280 million in 2016/17, and a restriction on the deductibility of corporate interest, which is estimated to raise £1 billion per annum. It also includes measures to extend UK withholding tax on royalties paid to low-tax jurisdictions</p><p> </p><p>The UK continues to engage with international efforts to improve adherence to international tax standards, including through the EU list of non-cooperative jurisdictions which was agreed by EU Finance Ministers in December last year.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-03-01T13:05:51.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847042/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847042/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847042/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-22","Tax Havens: Withholding Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make an assessment of the potential merits for tackling offshore tax avoidance and evasion of the imposition of a withholding tax on all interest and dividend payments to people and companies in tax havens which reject reform.","false","Biography information for Faisal Rashid","Warrington South","Faisal Rashid","129216"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847043","HM Treasury","false","2018-02-27","<p>Offshore Corporation Tax (including Supplementary Charge) is paid by companies exploring and producing oil and gas from the UK and the UK Continental Shelf. The number of companies that used field and investment allowances to reduce their Supplementary Charge liabilities in 2015-16 was 48. Data to assess the number of companies claiming the relief in 2016-17 and 2017-18 is not yet available.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-02-27T16:00:38.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847043/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847043/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847043/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-22","Offshore Industry: Corporation Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received relief from corporation tax on offshore (North Sea) CT reduction in Supplementary Charge arising from field and investment allowances in (a) 2015-16, (b) 2016-17 and (c) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","129217"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847044","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-01","<p>The National Living Wage is applicable to those aged 25 and over.</p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-03-01T16:10:14.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847044/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847044/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847044/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-22","Living Wage: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent estimate he has made of the proportion of people under the age of 25 who are in full time work and are not in receipt of the National Living Wage.","false","Biography information for Laura Pidcock","North West Durham","Laura Pidcock","129218"
