"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847056","HM Treasury","false","2018-03-01","<p>In the UK, only the Royal Mail are able to apply the exemption from value added tax on postal services.</p><p> </p><p>The details that HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) collects from taxpayers on their VAT returns are not specific enough to provide the number of people benefiting from this relief. HMRC does not require this level of detail because it would place a considerable administrative burden on businesses.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-03-01T12:56:39.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847056/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847056/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847056/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-22","Postal Services: VAT Exemptions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received an exemption from value added tax on postal services in (a) 2015-16, (b) 2016-17 and (c) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","129230"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847057","HM Treasury","false","2018-02-27","<p>Information on the number of parents eligible for Tax-Free Childcare by constituency is not available at the current time.</p><p> </p><p>Regarding the number of parents who have used childcare vouchers in the Wakefield constituency, I refer the Honourable Member to the answer I gave on 25 January 2017 to the Honourable Member for Hull North (123405).</p><p> </p><p>Parents currently receiving vouchers can continue to do so while they work for the same employer and that employer continues to offer them. HM Revenue &amp; Customs have published guidance and written to employers, who operate the schemes, to make sure that they are aware of the changes.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","129224 ; 129229","2018-02-27T14:11:01.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847057/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847057/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847057/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-22","Child Care Vouchers: Wakefield","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many families in Wakefield constituency have been written to in order to inform them that the Childcare Vouchers scheme is closing to new entrants on 5 April 2018.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","129231"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847058","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-02-27","<p>There were no deportation flights from RAF Northolt in 2017 for failed asylum seekers.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-02-27T14:35:31.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847058/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847058/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847058/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-22","RAF Northolt","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost to his Department is for deportation flights from RAF Northolt for failed asylum seekers in each month in 2017.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","129232"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847059","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>We fully support UN Special Envoy Staffan De Mistura and are in regular contact with him to discuss the Syrian political process. We support an inclusive political process as set out in UN Security Council Resolution 2254. It is vital that the political settlement to the Syrian conflict protects the rights of all components of Syrian society. Decisions on when and how to include any particular group in discussions are for the UN Special Envoy to take.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-02-27T17:32:14.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847059/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847059/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847059/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-22","Syria: Peace Negotiations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations his Department has made to the United Nations Special Envoy for Syria on the inclusion of (a) the Democratic Union Party and (b) the People's Protection Units in the Geneva process; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","129233"
