"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847064","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-03-01","<p>Defra’s finance system does not record whether a supplier provides fair trade products. To ascertain whether such products have been provided would require the manual examination of thousands of transactions. This information could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-03-01T17:58:09.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847064/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847064/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847064/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-02-22","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Fairtrade Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of his Department's spend on day-to-day goods has comprised fair trade products in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129238"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847065","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union is fully committed to ethical procurement, but does not hold information at the level of detail required to answer the Question.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2018-03-01T17:26:42.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847065/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847065/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847065/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-02-22","Department for Exiting the European Union: Fairtrade Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what proportion of his Department's spend on day-to-day goods has comprised fair trade products since it was established.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847066","Department for International Development","false","2018-03-01","<p>DFID has contracted Interserve Facilities Management to deliver catering facilities to our UK buildings with effect from 01 October 2016. We do not hold any data relevant to your request prior to this date. For the period from 01/10/16 to date we hold the following information:</p><p>DFID’s spend on catering products for this period was £427,396. The proportion of this spent on Fair Trade or Rainforest Alliance Products was £35,074 or 8.2%</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-03-01T17:12:48.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847066/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847066/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847066/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-02-22","Department for International Development: Fairtrade Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what proportion of her Department's spend on day-to-day goods has comprised fair trade products in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129240"
