"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847094","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-03-01","<p>The information requested is not held centrally. Day to day food products are purchased by an external catering supplier.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-03-01T17:16:16.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847094/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847094/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847094/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-02-22","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Fair Trade Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what proportion of his Department's spend on day-to-day goods comprised fair trade products in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847095","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-02","<p>The information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-03-02T14:20:22.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847095/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847095/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847095/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-02-22","Ministry of Justice: Fair Trade Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what proportion of his Department's spend on day-to-day goods comprised fair trade products in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847096","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-03-02","<p>The Northern Ireland Office is fully committed to ethical procurement; however, we are unable to quantify what proportion of our annual spend relates to fair trade products over the requested period.</p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2018-03-02T10:27:19.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847096/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847096/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847096/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-02-22","Northern Ireland Office: Fairtrade Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what proportion of his Department's spend on day-to-day goods comprised fair trade products in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847097","Wales Office","false","2018-03-02","<p>The Wales Office does not routinely spend on day-to-day food and drink products and uses Ministry of Justice contracts to procure most of our non-food day-to-day goods.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-03-02T09:56:24.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847097/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847097/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847097/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-02-22","Wales Office: Fairtrade Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what proportion of his Department's spend on day-to-day goods comprised fair trade products in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847098","Scotland Office","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Scotland Office does not have canteen facilities. The only expenditure on food is purchases for occasional events and receptions. The Scotland Office does not keep separate records of the spending on fair trade products. Spending on food follows Government policy on sustainability and Fair Trade.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-03-01T11:55:01.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847098/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847098/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847098/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-02-22","Scotland Office: Fairtrade Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what proportion of his Department's spend on day-to-day goods comprised fair trade products in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847099","Cabinet Office","false","2018-04-09","<p>All contracts over £10,000 are published on Contracts Finder, which you can find here; https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-04-09T10:27:54.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847099/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847099/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847099/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-22","Cabinet Office: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what organisations his Department has outsourced functions to since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847100","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS) is the amalgamation of the former Department of Energy and Climate Change (DECC) and Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) and was created in July 2016.</p><p> </p><p>Since the creation of BEIS the following functions have been outsourced:</p><p>CGI IT UK Limited – Payroll Services;</p><p>Capita Business Services Limited – Recruitment;</p><p>Clarity Travel Management – Business Travel;</p><p>My Civil Service Pension - Pensions Advice;</p><p>UK Shared Business Services (UK SBS) - Financial Transaction Services;</p><p>UK SBS – Procurement Services;</p><p>Engie UK - Facilities Management Services;</p><p>Shared Services Connect Limited – Financial Transaction Services;</p><p>Iron Mountain – Document Storage;</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-03-01T15:27:08.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847100/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847100/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847100/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-22","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what organisations his Department has outsourced functions to since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847101","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-02","<p>DCMS has not outsourced functions since 2011.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-03-02T09:46:55.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847101/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847101/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847101/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-02-22","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what organisations his Department has outsourced functions to since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129275"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847102","Department for Education","false","2018-03-02","<p>Since 2011, the department has entered shared services arrangements for two functions – the management of its estate and its human resources casework support. These are both with the Ministry of Justice. It has also outsourced two activities. The first was the analysis of 2016 key stage 2 science sampling test outcomes. This is a biennial activity and was outsourced to the National Foundation for Educational Research in 2016. The second activity is the administration of student support programmes for young people. This was contracted to Capita in 2015. The contract is currently out for re-tendering again with a start date of 2019.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-03-02T13:55:36.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847102/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847102/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847102/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-02-22","Department for Education: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what organisations his Department has outsourced functions to since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129276"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847103","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union uses a number of shared services. This includes the following OGDs: Department for International Trade (Commercial), Ministry of Justice (Estates Management) and Cabinet Office (IT), and private companies: Shared Services Connect Limited (elements of Finance, Payroll, HR).</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2018-03-01T17:17:12.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847103/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847103/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847103/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-02-22","Department for Exiting the European Union: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what organisations his Department has outsourced functions to since it was established.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129277"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847104","Department for International Development","false","2018-03-01","<p>Since 2011, the Department has outsourced one function (portering and mail services) to Interserve.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-03-01T17:31:31.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847104/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847104/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847104/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-02-22","Department for International Development: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will list the organisations her Department has outsourced functions to since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129278"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847105","Department for International Trade","false","2018-03-02","<p>The Department for International Trade has not outsourced any core internal functions since it was formally established in 2016 but we did inherit some outsourced contracts from UK Trade and Investment and the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills.</p><p>These included some contracts related to Trade promotion work in the UK, and overseas, and corporate services such as HR, IT and Finance functions.</p><p>A portion of these contracts have been re-negotiated or re-let since the Department was formed.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-03-02T14:54:11.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847105/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847105/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847105/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-02-22","Department for International Trade: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, to which organisations his Department has outsourced functions since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847106","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-02","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-03-02T11:18:45.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847106/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847106/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847106/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-22","Department for Transport: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, to which organisations his Department has outsourced functions since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847107","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Department is unable to answer the question as our e-procurement system only holds contractual information where the Department has entered into a contractual relationship with a supplier. This does not identify if a function is outsourced.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-03-01T15:30:23.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847107/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847107/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847107/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-22","Department for Work and Pensions: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, to which organisations her Department has outsourced functions since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129281"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847108","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-28","<p>The Department's central procurement system does not have a separate category for business process outsourcing (private companies delivering services previously provided by the public sector), nor any central means of consistently identifying outsourced services.</p><p> </p><p>To provide a comprehensive list would mean going back to each business area and Directorate in the Department and consulting on which of the contracts they have commissioned are to be considered to be business process outsourcing. This would incur disproportionate costs to produce.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-02-28T12:57:58.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847108/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847108/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847108/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-22","Department of Health and Social Care: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, to which organisations his Department has outsourced functions since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129282"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847109","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-02","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office has outsourced the service integration and management of its Global IT providers via BAE Systems since 2013.</p><p>More individual overseas posts might also have put local outsourcing arrangements in place, but we do not hold the data for this centrally, and it would incur disproportionate cost to provide an answer on that basis.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-03-02T13:45:26.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847109/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847109/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847109/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-22","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, to which organisations his Department has outsourced functions since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129283"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847110","HM Treasury","false","2018-03-02","<p>In 2017 the Treasury outsourced the Equitable Life Payment Scheme (ELPS) to Capita Employee Benefits Ltd.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-03-02T12:48:56.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847110/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847110/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847110/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-22","Treasury: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, to which organisations his Department has outsourced functions since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847111","Home Office","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Home Office has since 2010, published details of its contracts over £10,000 on the Pan-Gov’t Contracts Finder portal, as part of the HMT Transparency Agenda.</p><p>The link to the portal is as follows: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder</a></p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-03-01T19:10:44.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847111/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847111/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847111/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-22","Home Office: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, to which organisations her Department has outsourced functions since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847112","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-03-01","<p>Please see the attached list of organisations to which the Department has outsources services since 2011.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-03-01T17:15:09.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847112/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847112/answer","129286.doc","List of Organisations","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847112/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-02-22","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, to which organisations his Department has outsourced functions since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847113","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-02","<p>The requested information is not stored centrally. The MoJ would be required to write to each business within MoJ to advise what works has been outsourced since 2011 and the information requested could therefore only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-03-02T14:55:47.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847113/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847113/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847113/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-02-22","Ministry of Justice: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, to which organisations his Department has outsourced functions since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129287"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847114","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-03-02","<p>Since 2011, the Northern Ireland Office has used two centres of procurement excellence. The Central Procurement <a href="https://www.finance-ni.gov.uk/central-procurement-directorate" target="_blank">Division</a> and Crown Commercial <a href="http://ccs-agreements.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/suppliers" target="_blank">Services</a>, provide procurement oversight for the full range of outsourced services for the department.</p><p> </p><p>Both organisations publish relevant details on their websites for which the links have been provided. This includes any collaborative contracts which the department may use for additional outsourced functions.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2018-03-02T10:28:53.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847114/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847114/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847114/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-02-22","Northern Ireland Office: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, to which organisations his Department has outsourced functions since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847115","Wales Office","false","2018-03-02","<p>None. As a small Department, the Wales Office uses services provided by the Ministry of Justice in areas such as human resources, information technology, finance and facilities management.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-03-02T09:57:52.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847115/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847115/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847115/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-02-22","Wales Office: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, to which organisations his Department has outsourced functions since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847116","Scotland Office","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Scotland Office has not outsourced any functions since 2011.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-03-01T11:55:57.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847116/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847116/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847116/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-02-22","Scotland Office: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, if he will list the organisations that his Department has outsourced functions to since 2011.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129290"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847117","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-03-01","<p>The breakdown of staff employed in the department in each of the last eight years is shown below. Data is shown as at 31 March each year, except for the 2017/18 financial year which is shown as at 31 January 2018.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Headcount</strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017/18</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016/17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>20/1112</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010/11</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Full-Time Payroll staff</strong></p></td><td><p>3015</p></td><td><p>1678</p></td><td><p>1460</p></td><td><p>1818</p></td><td><p>1804</p></td><td><p>1899</p></td><td><p>1902</p></td><td><p>2238</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Part-Time Payroll staff</strong></p></td><td><p>548</p></td><td><p>272</p></td><td><p>238</p></td><td><p>268</p></td><td><p>264</p></td><td><p>272</p></td><td><p>262</p></td><td><p>315</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total Payroll Staff</strong></p></td><td><p>3563</p></td><td><p>1950</p></td><td><p>1968</p></td><td><p>2086</p></td><td><p>2068</p></td><td><p>2171</p></td><td><p>2164</p></td><td><p>2553</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Temporary staff</strong></p><p><strong>(non-payroll)</strong></p></td><td><p>339</p></td><td><p>121</p></td><td><p>75</p></td><td><p>98</p></td><td><p>91</p></td><td><p>73</p></td><td><p>73</p></td><td><p>119</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Zero-Hours</strong></p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total All Staff</strong></p></td><td><p>3902</p></td><td><p>2071</p></td><td><p>2043</p></td><td><p>2184</p></td><td><p>2159</p></td><td><p>2244</p></td><td><p>2237</p></td><td><p>2672</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Increases in payroll staff and temporary (non-payroll) numbers between 2016/17 and 2017/18 are due to recruitment to support EU Exit, corporate services transformation and prioritisation of work between the Arm’s Length Bodies / Executive Agencies and the department to support work on EU Exit.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>It is not Defra Policy to employ staff on “Zero-Hours” contracts.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-03-01T13:35:46.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847117/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847117/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847117/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-02-22","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Zero Hours Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many (a) full-time staff, (b) part-time staff, (c) temporary staff and (d) any other staff on zero hour contracts were employed directly by their Department in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847118","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-14","<p>The Cabinet Office does not collect and retain information on trade union membership within the department.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-03-14T14:24:44.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847118/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847118/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847118/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-22","Cabinet Office: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what percentage of workers employed directly by his Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847119","Home Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Immigration Act 2014 is the primary legislation which gives the Home Office statutory powers to set fees for all immigration and nationality applications. The relevant sections of the Act relating to fees are 68 to 70 which can be found on pages 58 to 61 of the following link.</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2014/22/pdfs/ukpga_20140022_en.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2014/22/pdfs/ukpga_20140022_en.pdf</a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-02-27T17:27:35.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847119/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847119/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847119/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-22","Visas: Overseas Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant the the Answer of 15 January 2018 to Question 121748, what criteria her Department uses for setting overseas student fees if visa income is not differentiated between the various categories in which they are received.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","129293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847120","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS) was created on 14 July 2016. The Department of Energy and Climate Change (DECC) and the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) were merged to create this new department.</p><p> </p><p>BEIS does not hold data on the number of workers employed by the department that belong to a trade union.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-03-01T10:35:47.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847120/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847120/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847120/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-22","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what percentage of workers employed by his Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847121","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-02","<p>The Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport (DCMS) has limited information, presented in the table below. However information is not held on those employees who chose to pay their trade union subscriptions themselves directly through direct debit to their trade union. Therefore an accurate overall percentage figure cannot be given, as it would not include these employees.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DCMS Staff</p></td><td><p>400</p></td><td><p>394</p></td><td><p>475</p></td><td><p>527</p></td><td><p>656</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Percentage belonging to a trade union</p></td><td><p>29%</p></td><td><p>37%</p></td><td><p>28%</p></td><td><p>20%</p></td><td><p>13%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>This data is based on the position at 31st March in each of the years given and the number of staff who paid their trade union subscriptions through the payroll. This includes permanent staff, those on fixed-term contracts, those on paid loan/secondment in/out of DCMS and those on paid maternity leave.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-03-02T09:56:25.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847121/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847121/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847121/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-02-22","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what percentage of workers employed directly by his Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847122","Department for Education","false","2018-03-02","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-03-02T14:27:06.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847122/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847122/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847122/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-02-22","Department for Education: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what percentage of workers employed directly by his Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847123","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Department does not have a check-off facility for the deduction of trade union subscriptions from departmental employees pay, therefore a complete set of data to give an accurate figure for the percentage of employees who are trade union members for the period requested is not held by the Department.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2018-03-01T17:23:56.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847123/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847123/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847123/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-02-22","Department for Exiting the European Union: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what percentage of workers employed directly by his Department belonged to a trade union in each year since its formation.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129297"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847124","Department for International Development","false","2018-03-01","<p>DFID do not hold this information. Trade union membership is held by the individual trade union.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-03-01T17:23:11.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847124/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847124/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847124/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-02-22","Department for International Development: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what percentage of workers employed directly by her Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847125","Department for International Trade","false","2018-03-06","<p>The Department for International Trade (DIT) was established in July 2016. The percentage of workers who are trade union members is not held by DIT.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-03-06T13:28:21.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847125/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847125/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847125/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-02-22","Department for International Trade: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what percentage of workers employed directly by his Department belonged to a trade union in each year since his Department's formation.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129299"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847126","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-02","<p>We do not hold records of all civil servants within the Department for Transport who are members of trade unions.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-03-02T11:26:59.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847126/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847126/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847126/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-22","Department for Transport: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what percentage of workers employed directly by his Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847127","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-01","<p>The check off facility for the deduction of trade union subscriptions from departmental employees pay ended 30 April 2015. An accurate figure for the percentage of employees who are trade union members for the period requested is not held by the Department.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-03-01T15:35:19.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847127/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847127/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847127/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-22","Department for Work and Pensions: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what percentage of workers employed directly by her Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129301"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847128","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-28","<p>The Department holds the following information presented in the table, however information is not held on those employees who chose to pay their trade union subscriptions themselves directly through direct debit to their trade union. Therefore an accurate overall percentage figure cannot be given as it does not include these employees.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Month</p></td><td><p>Headcount (Civil Servants only)</p></td><td><p>Total Trade Union Subscriptions Paid Via Payroll Deductions</p></td><td><p>% Of Total Headcount</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January-2018</p></td><td><p>1,514</p></td><td><p>258</p></td><td><p>17.0%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January -2017</p></td><td><p>1,796</p></td><td><p>567</p></td><td><p>31.6%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January -2016</p></td><td><p>2,004</p></td><td><p>609</p></td><td><p>30.4%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January -2015</p></td><td><p>2,024</p></td><td><p>609</p></td><td><p>30.1%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January -2014</p></td><td><p>1,927</p></td><td><p>718</p></td><td><p>37.3%</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-02-28T12:59:57.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847128/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847128/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847128/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-22","Department of Health and Social Care: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what percentage of workers employed directly by his Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847129","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-02","<p>​This information is not held by the Foreign and Commonwealth Office. Staff pay subscriptions themselves to their trade union.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-03-02T13:47:11.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847129/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847129/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847129/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-22","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what percentage of workers employed directly by his Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129303"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847130","HM Treasury","false","2018-03-02","<p>The information requested is not available.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-03-02T13:17:16.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847130/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847130/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847130/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-22","Treasury: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what percentage of workers employed directly by his Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129304"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847131","Home Office","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Home Office does not hold this data. All of those Home Office employees who belong to a trade union now pay their subscriptions direct to these unions by direct debit. The Home Office therefore does not have access to this membership information.</p><p>The check-off trade union subscription facility, which enabled trade union members to have their membership subscriptions deducted via the departmental payroll, was removed in January 2015. Check-off records would have provided incomplete data on the number of employees belonging to a trade union as some trade union members would have been subscribing to their union by other means, such as direct debit.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-03-01T19:12:38.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847131/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847131/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847131/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-22","Home Office: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what percentage of workers employed directly by her Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129305"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847132","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-03-05","<p>The Department does not have a complete set of data for this information as we are not notified of individuals who may choose to pay their trade union membership via direct debit and as such is unable to answer your question.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-03-05T16:46:52.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847132/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847132/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847132/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-02-22","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what percentage of workers employed directly by his Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129306"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847133","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-02","<p>The only data held on this is at December 2014 when the number of staff within the MoJ (including HMPPS) that were members of trades unions was 43,286 which equated to 63.21% of staff numbers. Following the removal of check-off as a method of payment for members to pay for union subscriptions, it is no longer possible for the department to verify the numbers of staff that are currently trade union members.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-03-02T14:55:34.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847133/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847133/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847133/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-02-22","Ministry of Justice: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what percentage of workers employed directly by his Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129307"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847134","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-03-01","<p>In 2013/14, 31 members of my department belonged to a trade union.</p><p>In 2014/15, 29 members of my department belonged to a trade union.</p><p>At September 2015, 29 members of my department belonged to a trade union.</p><p> </p><p>No data is available for subsequent years as from September 2015 trade union deductions were made directly from employees’ bank accounts and not collected through my department’s payroll.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2018-03-01T11:22:26.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847134/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847134/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847134/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-02-22","Northern Ireland Office: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what percentage of workers employed directly by her Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847135","Wales Office","false","2018-03-02","<p>The Wales Office does not record how many of its staff are members of a trade union. The Department is not an employer in its own right and most of our staff are employed by the Ministry of Justice (MOJ).</p><p> </p><p>The MOJ held data until December 2014 on the number of staff (including Wales Office staff) who were members of a trade union. However, following the removal of check-off as a method of payment for members to pay for union subscriptions it is no longer possible to verify the numbers of staff that are trade union members.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-03-02T09:59:10.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847135/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847135/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847135/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-02-22","Wales Office: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what percentage of workers employed directly by his Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129309"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847136","Scotland Office","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Scotland Office does not employ staff directly; all staff that join do so on an assignment, loan or secondment from other Government bodies. The Scotland Office does not hold information on trade union membership.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-03-01T11:56:53.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847136/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847136/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847136/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-02-22","Scotland Office: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what percentage of workers employed directly by his Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847137","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-03-01","<p>The “check off” facility, which allowed for the deduction of trade union subscriptions from departmental employees pay, ended on 31 January 2015. Therefore a complete set of data to give an accurate figure for the percentage of employees who were trade union members for the period requested is not held by the department.</p><p> </p><p>At the point of check off removal on 31 January 2015, Defra and its agencies had approximately 36% of employees paying trade union subscriptions through check off.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-03-01T17:34:51.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847137/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847137/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847137/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-02-22","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what percentage of workers employed directly by his Department belonged to a trade union in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847138","Department for Education","false","2018-03-02","<p>The Disability Access Fund (DAF) is allocated and paid to local authorities as part of the Dedicated Schools Grant (DSG). The provisional DAF allocations to each local authority for financial year 2017 to 2018 are available in the ‘DSG allocations: 2017 to 2018’ table on GOV.UK at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dedicated-schools-grant-dsg-2017-to-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dedicated-schools-grant-dsg-2017-to-2018</a>. The Education and Skills Funding Agency pays DSG to local authorities in 25 instalments during the financial year. The DSG payment dates for financial year 2017 to 2018 are in Annex A of the ‘DSG: conditions of grant 2017 to 2018’ GOV.UK at the link above.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-02T11:39:37.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847138/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847138/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847138/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-02-22","Pre-school Education: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much money has been paid as part of the disability access fund to each local authority in each month since April 2017.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","129312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847139","Home Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>As my earlier answer of 20 February 2018 to the honourable member stated, detainee welfare concerns in Immigration Removal Centres can be raised at any point, to the Home Office, NHS (England) or the custodial supplier as appropriate. The BBC first made the Home Office aware of the specific issues later aired by Panorama on 24 August 2017. The Government takes the health and welfare of immigration detainees very seriously and expects the highest standards from those who manage the detention estate on its behalf.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-02-27T17:24:59.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847139/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847139/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847139/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-22","Brook House Immigration Removal Centre","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 20 February 2018 to Question 127772, whether her Department was aware of concerns about detainee welfare at Brook House Immigration Removal Centre before the BBC alerted it to the specific issues raised on Panorama on 24 August 2017.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","129313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847140","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-02","<p>I refer my Rt. Hon Friend to my response to his previous question on 15 January 2018 (PQ 121105).</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-03-02T13:52:10.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847140/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847140/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847140/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-22","Burma: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 15 January 2018 to Question 121105, whether the British Embassy or other UK Government offices in Myanmar purchased any goods or services from military-owned or controlled companies.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","129314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847141","Home Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Home Office records and publishes data, broken down by nationality, of all those who make an asylum claim or are referred to the National Referral mechanism (NRM) as a potential victim of trafficking or modern slavery. Information concerning a claimants route of travel to the United Kingdom is not recorded centrally in a readily accessible format, and could only be provided at disproportionate costs by examination of individual interview transcripts and case files.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-02-27T17:25:38.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847141/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847141/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847141/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-22","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 1 February 2018 to Question 125290, what assessment her Department has made of the potential merit of recording the country of origin of illegally trafficked people who have been granted asylum.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","129315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847142","Home Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Gateway Protection Programme demonstrates the UK’s proud tradition of providing protection to refugees. Details on the number of refugees resettled under this scheme are published as part of the quarterly Immigration Statistics release, available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/immigration-statistics-quarterly-release" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/immigration-statistics-quarterly-release</a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-02-27T17:02:39.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847142/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847142/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847142/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-22","Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many refugees have been resettled under the Gateway Protection Programme.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","129316"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847143","Department for Transport","true","2018-02-27","<p>The numbers of reported cyclist fatalities and serious injuries that have been recorded in Great Britain for each year since 2007 where poorly maintained roads could be considered to be a contributory factor is provided in the table. A breakdown for all the road networks specified is not available centrally.</p><p><ins class="ministerial">The heading “Poor or defective road surface” cover columns 2 and 3 of the table. Whilst, the heading “Inadequate or masked signs or road markings” cover column 4 and 5.</ins></p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="6"><p><strong>Reported cyclist serious and fatal injuries in GB where poorly maintained roads is reported as a contributory factor<sup>1</sup></strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><p><strong>Poor or defective road surface </strong></p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>Inadequate or masked signs or road markings</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Reported Cyclist Fatilities</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Reported Cyclist Serious Injuries</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Reported Cyclist Fatilities</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Reported Cyclist Serious Injuries</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>15</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>29</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>25</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>42</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>41</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>38</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>55</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>45</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>60</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="5"><p><strong><em>Source: DfT STATS19 reported road casualties</em></strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><sup>1 </sup>Includes only casualties where a police officer attended the scene and in which a contributory factor was reported. In 2016, this related to 73% of reported accidents.</p><p> </p><p>By way of context, cycling in Great Britain has increased over the time period in question, rising from 4 billion kilometres in 2007 to 6 billion kilometres in 2016.</p><p> </p><p>It should be that noted that contributory factors assigned by police officers do not assign blame for the accident to any specific road user, however they do provide some insight into why and how road accidents occur. They give an indication of which factors the attending officer thought contributed to the accident. Officers do not need to carry out a full investigation of the incident before allocating contributory factors; they usually use professional judgement about what they can see at the scene.</p><p> </p><p>Not all accidents are included in the contributory factor data; only accidents where the police attended the scene and reported at least one contributory factor are included. A total of 73% of accidents reported to the police in 2016 met these criteria although each accident can have multiple contributory factors attributed to them.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-02-27T16:45:50.58Z","2018-03-15T15:22:13.737Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847143/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847143/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847143/answer","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847143/answer/previousversion/43590","Biography information for Jesse Norman","27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-22","Cycling: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many cyclists have died or suffered serious injuries where the cause has been attributed to poorly-maintained roads by (a) local councils, (b) Highways England, (c) Transport Scotland and (d) the Welsh Government in each year since 2007.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","129317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847144","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-12","<p>There are no employees in my department who are currently, or have previously been, employed on zero-hours contracts in the last eight years.</p><p> </p><p>The report can be found here:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/people-in-employment-on-a-zero-hours-contract-mar-2017</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-03-12T14:01:50.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847144/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847144/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847144/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-22","Cabinet Office: Zero Hours Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many (a) full-time staff, (b) part-time staff, (c) temporary staff and (d) any other staff were directly employed on zero-hours contracts by his Department in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847145","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-01","<p>As the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS) was created in July 2016, eight years data is not available. In the period since then, BEIS has not directly employed its staff using zero-hours contracts.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-03-01T11:12:17.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847145/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847145/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847145/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-22","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Zero Hours Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many (a) full-time staff, (b) part-time staff, (c) temporary staff and (d) any other staff were directly employed on zero-hours contracts by his Department in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129319"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847146","Home Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Supreme Court judgment upholds the Court of Appeal judgment and the 2014 High Court judgment and means that claims against the police for serious failures in investigations can continue to be made.</p><p>The Government welcomes the clarity provided by the Supreme Court judgment in emphasising the high threshold for such claims i.e. where there are serious failures or shortcomings in investigations engaging Article 3 of the European Convention on Human Rights. This provides the police with greater clarity as to when claims can be made.</p><p>We will continue to work with the National Police Chiefs’ Council to monitor current claims and assess any impacts as a result of future action taken against forces on the basis of this ruling.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","129347","2018-02-27T17:45:48.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847146/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847146/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847146/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-22","John Worboys","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the judgment of Commissioner of Police of the Metropolis (Appellant) v DSD and another (Respondents) [2018] UKSC 11, whether she plans to conduct a resource impact assessment into the capacity of the police service as a result of that decision.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","129320"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847147","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-02","<p>The number of (a) full-time staff, (b) part-time staff, (c) temporary staff, and (d) any other staff directly employed on zero-hours contracts is given below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(a) Full-time</p></td><td><p>440</p></td><td><p>400</p></td><td><p>420</p></td><td><p>360</p></td><td><p>346</p></td><td><p>421</p></td><td><p>483</p></td><td><p>595</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(b) Part-time</p></td><td><p>50</p></td><td><p>50</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>48</p></td><td><p>54</p></td><td><p>44</p></td><td><p>61</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(c) Temporary staff</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>35</p></td><td><p>51</p></td><td><p>68</p></td><td><p>54</p></td><td><p>54</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(d) Zero-hour contracts</p></td><td><p>✝</p></td><td><p>✝</p></td><td><p>✝</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>This data is based on the position at 31st March in each of the years given. The full-time and part-time figures include Civil Servants on DCMS’ payroll. This includes permanent staff, those on fixed-term contracts, those on paid loan/secondment in/out of DCMS and those on paid maternity leave.</p><p> </p><p>Exact headcount is given for 2014 to 2017 based on data DCMS currently holds. Figures are rounded to the nearest 10 for full-time and part-time staff for 2010 to 2013 as this information is taken from data published in the Annual Civil Service Employment Survey. This data source can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/query/construct/summary.asp?mode=construct&amp;version=0&amp;dataset=129" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/query/construct/summary.asp?mode=construct&amp;version=0&amp;dataset=129</a></p><p> </p><p>Data is based on the position at 31st March in each year so 2018 data is not yet available. This data will be uploaded to this website later in 2018.</p><p> </p><p>* Information on temporary staff is taken from the Workforce Management Information which DCMS produces on a monthly basis and publishes annually. This information was not produced before 2013.</p><p> </p><p>✝ Information on zero-hour contracts is not available before 2013.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-03-02T09:44:04.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847147/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847147/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847147/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-02-22","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Zero Hours Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many (a) full-time staff, (b) part-time staff, (c) temporary staff and (d) any other staff were directly employed on zero-hours contracts by his Department in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129321"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847148","Department for Education","false","2018-03-02","<p>The department does not directly employ any staff on zero hours contracts, and has not done so in any of the last eight years.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-03-02T14:39:17.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847148/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847148/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847148/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-02-22","Department for Education: Zero Hours Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many (a) full-time staff, (b) part-time staff, (c) temporary staff and (d) any other staff were directly employed on zero-hours contracts by his Department in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129322"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847149","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-03-01","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union does not employ any staff on zero hours contracts.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2018-03-01T17:21:53.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847149/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847149/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/847149/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-02-22","Department for Exiting the European Union: Zero Hours Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many (a) full-time staff, (b) part-time staff, (c) temporary staff and (d) any other staff were directly employed on zero-hours contracts by his Department in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","129323"
